## Path E — Scale Capacity (Bring in Help)

When the bottleneck is you and there's more work than you can take, bring in support. This is the "Integrator" role from EOS (Entrepreneurial Operating System) — someone who runs the daily execution while you hold the creative vision.

### Tasks:
1. **Identify your Queen Bee Role** — strategy, creative direction, client relationships. These stay with you.
2. **Identify what can be delegated** — production design (final files, asset prep), web dev (Squarespace, Shopify templates), admin (scheduling, invoicing), outreach email drafting (automate with AI).
3. **Build a trusted freelancer bench** — find 1–2 junior designers or web devs you can sub to. Test on a low-risk project. Pay properly.
4. **Document your process as SOPs** — if someone can't follow your process from written notes, it can't be delegated. Start with the Alt Cosmetics project as the first SOP template. Aim: one SOP per service type.
5. **Consider a part-time Integrator** — once there's enough work, someone to handle scheduling, invoicing, basic client comms, and admin. Even 5hrs/week changes the equation.

